1111 Park Avenue, at S. E. corner of 90th street, a new apartment building, nearing completion, replacing four 5-story houses on Park Avenue and Nos. 104-10 East 90th Street. The building immediately below it is only two or three years older.

1925.

722366f-a.text:
1112 Park Avenue, on S.W. corner of 90th Street, newly completed, replacing two 5-story buildings. In 1930 the 7-story double apartment house (Meteor) on the N.W. corner of 89th Street will be replaced by a 17-story building, but the two little
houses in between will stay.
1927.
Knickerbocker Photo Service.
